library("dplyr")
library("stringr")
library("ggplot2")


# Data from reddit user austingwalters in this reddit thread: https://www.reddit.com/r/udub/comments/4e6kxl/i_made_a_website_that_shows_grade_distributions/
# Dataset and FOIA info from their dropbox: https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/8lbyazjlt5jmv86jvvs06/AGtgMaWeyZtZuS2fSYLYn_4?dl=0&e=1&rlkey=1sg7t372nhslxogwjl3e9lt9t

uw_grades_original_df <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kylethayer/Info-201-au-24-datasets/refs/heads/main/UW-Seattle_20110-20161-Course-Grade-Data_2016-04-06.csv", check.names=FALSE)
 
# From Course_Number get program abbreviation (Program_Abv) and number (Course_Number_Num)
# From Term get Term_Season
uw_grades_df <- uw_grades_original_df |> 
  mutate(
    Program_Abv = str_split_i(Course_Number, " ", 1),
    Course_Number_Num = as.integer(str_extract(Course_Number, "\\d+")),
    Term_Season = str_extract(Term, "Autumn|Spring|Summer|Winter")
  )

Overall Grade Distribution Summary

Number of courses in the dataset

Total_Courses <- nrow(uw_grades_df)
Total_Courses
[1] 39242

Average of the average GPA across all courses

Avg_GPA <- 
  uw_grades_df |>
  pull(Average_GPA) |>
  mean(na.rm = TRUE) |>
  round(digits = 2)
Avg_GPA
[1] 3.41

Average number of students in courses

Avg_Course_Students <- 
  uw_grades_df |>
  pull(Student_Count) |>
  mean(na.rm = TRUE) |>
  round(digits = 2)
Avg_Course_Students
[1] 45.38

Minimum Course Number

Min_Course_Number <-
  uw_grades_df |>
  pull(Course_Number_Num) |>
  min(na.rm=TRUE)
Min_Course_Number
[1] 100

Maximum Course Number

Max_Course_Number <-
  uw_grades_df |>
  pull(Course_Number_Num) |>
  max(na.rm=TRUE)
Max_Course_Number
[1] 750

Histogram of average GPA across all courses

ggplot(uw_grades_df) + 
  geom_histogram(aes(x = Average_GPA),binwidth = 0.1) +
  labs(
    title = "Average GPA Across All Courses",
    x = "Average GPA",
    y = "Number of Course"
  )

Scatterplot of average GPA and student count

ggplot(uw_grades_df) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = Student_Count,y = Average_GPA)) +
  labs(
    title = "Student Count vs. Average GPA",
    x = "Student Count",
    y = "Average GPA"
  )

Look over the averages and graphs, there are 39242 courses, each having on average 45.38 students. The average GPA across all these courses is 3.41. The minimum course number is 100 and the maximum is 750. Comparing these numbers to the graphs shows that the results are pretty consistent.
